dct_description_sm: Relief shown by contours and hachures. Printed on two sheets joined together to form one map. In note: "Hē ergasia ērchise ton Septembrion 1945 eperatōthē ton Febrouarion 1947 kai exetupōthē eis prōtēn eudosin eis duo fulla klim. 1:40000 kai hena fullon klim. 1:5000. Η εργασία ήρχισε τόν Σεπτέμβριον 1945 επερατώθη τόν Φεβρουάριον 1947 καί εξετυπώθη είς πρώτην εύδοσιν είς δύο φύλλα κλιμ. 1:40000 καί ένα φύλλον κλιμ. 1:50000. The work began in September 1945, was completed in February 1947, and was printed in the first edition on two sheets: one 1:40000 scale, one 1:50000 scale. Principal meridian is Athens. 23°42ʹ58.3″ east of Greenwich. Relief shown by contours. In note: SĒM ... 1945, 1947.
